From Lars Henrik Eriksson Subject Re How universal are phones these days In article Wolfgang Diestelkamp writes In article Hugo Calendar writes I'm wondering if I can tote my American touch tone phone around with me to Sweden and It's DC powered and I can buy a special adapter for that in The question is if the general electronics work the I can buy a different wall plug and refit it I'm sure I'd have to but would that do the trick Two things to watch for In Germany and I think the same holds for Sweden only some of the connections can handle tone dialing so make sure the phone can be set to pulse Most if not virtually all swedish exchanges can handle tone Many older electromechanical exchanges have been modified accept tone Lars Henrik Eriksson Internet Swedish Institute of Computer Science Phone intn'l Box Telefon nat'l S KISTA SWEDEN Fax